* [[United States House Judiciary Subcommittee on Immigration Policy and Enforcement]], September 24, 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/09/24/AR2010092402734.html|title=Stephen Colbert, in GOP pundit character, testifies on immigration in D.C|publisher=Washington Post|date=September 25, 2010|accessdate=September 16, 2011|first=Dan|last=Zak}}</ref> However, Colbert did [[break character]] when he responded to questions by Congresswoman [[Judy Chu]] about the plight of immigrant workers.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediaite.com/tv/seriously-missed-stephen-colbert-broke-character-to-raise-plight-of-migrant-workers/|title=Seriously Missed: Stephen Colbert Broke Character Once To Raise Plight Of Migrant Workers|date=September 24, 2010|accessdate=September 16, 2011|first=Colby|last=Hall|publisher=[[Mediaite]]}}</ref>
