*''[[This Week with George Stephanopoulos]]'', January 15, 2012<ref>{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/OTUS/stephen-colbert-runs-president-talks-george-stephanopoulos/story?id=15363182#.TxWJLPlKRU0|title=Super PAC Satire: Colbert Explains (Faux) Presidential Run to ABC News|date=January 15, 2012}}</ref>
* A [[White House]] [[state dinner]] in honor of French president, [[Francois Hollande]], February 11, 2014. Colbert was seated at the head table, in a seat which would have gone to Hollande's guest had he brought one.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2014/02/bradley-cooper-stephen-colbert-state-dinner-guests-france-francois-hollande-barack-obama-103399.html|title=Bradley Cooper, Stephen Colbert among dinner guests|date=February 11, 2014|first=Lucy|last=McCalmont|publisher=[[Politico.com]]|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref> The following night, Colbert referenced on his show his seating assignment at the head table, calling himself the "First Lady of France".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/stephen-colbert-jokes-lady-france-article-1.1612718|title=Stephen Colbert celebrates his self-appointed role as First Lady of France|first=Leslie|last=Larson|date=February 13, 2014|location=New York|work=Daily News}}</ref>
* In 2014 the character was used in an ad campaign for Wonderful Pistachios, which lunched with a [[Super Bowl advertising|Super Bowl commercial]] that aired during [[Super Bowl XLVIII]]
*''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'', February 17, 2014, [[The first episode of The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon|the first episode]]. Fallon had several celebrities come on stage and give him $100 bills paying off bets that they lost because he got to host The Tonight Show. Colbert was the last celebrity and he came with $100 in a bucket of pennies, pouring them down Fallon's clothes.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nj.com/entertainment/tv/index.ssf/2014/02/rutgers_jimmy_fallon_u2_tonight_show.html|title=Jimmy Fallon 'Tonight Show' performance makes rock stars of Rutgers students|date=February 19, 2014|first=Amy|last=Kuperinsky|publisher=[[The Star-Ledger]]}}</ref>
*2014 [[RSA Conference]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediaite.com/online/watch-colbert-delivers-keynote-at-controversial-rsa-security-conference/|title=WATCH: Colbert Delivers Keynote at Controversial RSA Security Conference|first=Matt|last=Wilstein|date=March 1, 2014}}</ref>
*2014 [[San Diego Comic-Con International|Comic-con]]: appeared both as a panel moderator as well as in costume portraying a character called "Prince Hawkcat" which is supposed to be "Half Hawk. Half Cat. Whole Prince". The attendance in costume was not revealed until two months after the event.<ref>{{cite news|date=September 18, 2014|first=Patrick Kevin|last=Day|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/showtracker/la-et-st-stephen-colbert-comiccon-prince-hawkcat-20140918-story.html|publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]]|title=
Stephen Colbert walked the floor at Comic-Con as 'Prince Hawkcat'}}</ref>
*October 2014 [[Apple Inc.]] press event: Colbert participated in the event [[teleconference|via phone]] where he asked to be given the title "Supreme Allied Commander of Super Secrecy"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/missed-apple-event-ipads-stephen-colbert/story?id=26251723|title=What You Missed at the Apple Event: From New iPads to Stephen Colbert|date=Oct 16, 2014|first=Alyssa|last=Necomb|publisher=[[ABC News]]}}</ref>
* Colbert appeared in the November 6, 2014 episode of ''[[@midnight]]'' to announce the "Hashtag Wars" for the episode.<ref>''@midnight'' episode 156, aired November 6, 2014 on Comedy Central.</ref>
* Colbert made an appearance in the ''[[House of Cards (U.S. TV series)|House of Cards]]'' [[House of Cards (Season 3)|season three]] episode "Chapter 27". The segment was taped before ''The Colbert Report'' set was transformed into the set for ''The Nightly Show with Larry Wilmore''. It was first released on February 27, 2015, two months after [[The final episode of The Colbert Report|The final episode of ''The Colbert Report'']] aired, making it the final appearance of the character.<ref name=HouseofCards/>

